##id: cross_sample_mono_recipient
##description: Sample B mono-exon recipient (gene_id NOVEL_RECIPIENT) at chr1:10500-12500.
##description: Spans the donor's intron (chr1:11001-11999), so classify_mono_exon
##description: returns INTRON_RETENTION and the segment is created (not dropped).
##description: With the inheritance fix, B's segment adopts NOVEL_DONOR's gene_idx
##description: from the spatially-overlapping multi-exon segment; without the fix,
##description: candidates is empty for size-1 transcripts and B keeps its own
##description: gene_idx, inflating singleton-gene counts.
chr1	TEST	transcript	10500	12500	.	+	.	gene_id "NOVEL_RECIPIENT"; transcript_id "TX_MONO";
chr1	TEST	exon	10500	12500	.	+	.	gene_id "NOVEL_RECIPIENT"; transcript_id "TX_MONO"; exon_number "1";
